[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I've turned off notifications on my phone. No calls will ring, and it won't vibrate or light up.[l][r]
When I secretly go out to buy groceries or daily necessities, I keep an eye on notifications and call logs.[l][r]
I could check it in the bathroom too, but if I'm gone too long, Chii-chan might notice.[l][r]
[r]I try to keep Chii-chan talking as much as possible, have her read her favorite books to me, exhaust her, so she can sleep soundly.[l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
During that time, I make a quick trip to the convenience store to do the shopping. This has become my routine.[l][r]
[r]As for money, I asked Dad, who is in Hungary right now. I took a leave of absence from school and quit my part-time job.[l][r]
Everyone was worried. I apologized, saying sorry.[l][r]
[r]...Just wait a little longer, just a little more.[l][r]
I think that only when I'm out. When I get back to the room, I stop thinking about it.[l][r]

[cm]This life that can't go on forever.[l][r]
But I wasn't scared. Probably, Chii-chan was more frightened. That's why I wasn't scared.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

